PART VI. ISSUANCE OF BONDS

SECTION 14. AIRPORT REVENUE BONDS. The department of transportation is authorized to issue airport revenue bonds for airport capital improvement program projects authorized in part II and listed in part IV of this Act and designated to be financed by revenue bond funds or by general obligation bond funds.

The department may pay interest on airport revenue bonds during the estimated period of construction of the capital improvement program project for which such bonds are issued, to establish, maintain, or increase reserves for the bonds, and to pay the expenses of issuance. The airport revenue bonds shall be issued pursuant to part III of chapter 39, Hawaii Revised Statutes, as amended. The principal and interest on airport revenue bonds, to the extent not paid from the proceeds, shall be payable solely from and secured solely by revenues from airports and related facilities under the State’s ownership or operated and managed by the department, and aviation fuel taxes levied and paid pursuant to sections 243—4 (a) (2) and 248—8, Hawaii Revised Statutes, or parts thereof as the department may determine.  This includes rents, landing fees, and other fees or charges presently or hereafter derived from or arising through the ownership, operation, and management of airports and related facilities, the furnishing and supplying of services, and passenger facility charges pursuant to section 261-5.5, Hawaii Revised Statutes, as amended, and as determined by the department.
